<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="99" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,963,1062]" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,963,989]" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described based on a single specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[963,1014,964,990]" name="Peru" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1031,1095,963,989]" country="Peru" name="Puno" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">Puno</collectingRegion>
). It has been confused with an undescribed species from 
<collectingCountry box="[443,536,999,1025]" name="Ecuador" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1950" box="[591,820,999,1026]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscoapicalis" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[591,608,1000,1025]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">B</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[632,656,1000,1025]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[672,820,999,1025]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">fuscoapicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the collections (now being described by another author). The 
<typeStatus box="[270,368,1035,1061]" pageId="4" pageNumber="99">holotype</typeStatus>
is female, information not provided in the original description.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
